#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:2
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:5
msgid "Command line options and configuration file settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:7
msgid ""
"You can get help on command line and configuration options by using the "
"general help option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:9
msgid "pytest -h   # prints options _and_ config file settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:13
msgid ""
"This will display command line and configuration file settings which were "
"registered by installed plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:19
msgid "Configuration file formats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:21
msgid ""
"Many :ref:`pytest settings <ini options ref>` can be set in a *configuration "
"file*, which by convention resides in the root directory of your repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:24
msgid "A quick example of the configuration files supported by pytest:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:27
msgid "pytest.toml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:31
msgid ""
"``pytest.toml`` files take precedence over other files, even when empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:33
msgid "Alternatively, the hidden version ``.pytest.toml`` can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:37
msgid ""
"# pytest.toml or .pytest.toml\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"minversion = \"9.0\"\n"
"addopts = [\"-ra\", \"-q\"]\n"
"testpaths = [\n"
"    \"tests\",\n"
"    \"integration\",\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:49
msgid "pytest.ini"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:51
msgid ""
"``pytest.ini`` files take precedence over other files (except ``pytest."
"toml`` and ``.pytest.toml``), even when empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:53
msgid "Alternatively, the hidden version ``.pytest.ini`` can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:57
msgid ""
"# pytest.ini or .pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"minversion = 6.0\n"
"addopts = -ra -q\n"
"testpaths =\n"
"    tests\n"
"    integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:69
msgid "pyproject.toml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:74
msgid "``pyproject.toml`` files are supported for configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:78
msgid ""
"Use ``[tool.pytest]`` to leverage native TOML types (supported since pytest "
"9.0):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:80
msgid ""
"# pyproject.toml\n"
"[tool.pytest]\n"
"minversion = \"9.0\"\n"
"addopts = [\"-ra\", \"-q\"]\n"
"testpaths = [\n"
"    \"tests\",\n"
"    \"integration\",\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:93
msgid ""
"Use ``[tool.pytest.ini_options]`` for INI-style configuration (supported "
"since pytest 6.0):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:95
msgid ""
"# pyproject.toml\n"
"[tool.pytest.ini_options]\n"
"minversion = \"6.0\"\n"
"addopts = \"-ra -q\"\n"
"testpaths = [\n"
"    \"tests\",\n"
"    \"integration\",\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:107
msgid "tox.ini"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:109
msgid ""
"``tox.ini`` files are the configuration files of the `tox <https://tox."
"readthedocs.io>`__ project, and can also be used to hold pytest "
"configuration if they have a ``[pytest]`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:114
msgid ""
"# tox.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"minversion = 6.0\n"
"addopts = -ra -q\n"
"testpaths =\n"
"    tests\n"
"    integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:126
msgid "setup.cfg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:128
msgid ""
"``setup.cfg`` files are general purpose configuration files, used originally "
"by ``distutils`` (now deprecated) and :std:doc:`setuptools <setuptools:"
"userguide/declarative_config>`, and can also be used to hold pytest "
"configuration if they have a ``[tool:pytest]`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:133
msgid ""
"# setup.cfg\n"
"[tool:pytest]\n"
"minversion = 6.0\n"
"addopts = -ra -q\n"
"testpaths =\n"
"    tests\n"
"    integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:145
msgid ""
"Usage of ``setup.cfg`` is not recommended unless for very simple use cases. "
"``.cfg`` files use a different parser than ``pytest.ini`` and ``tox.ini`` "
"which might cause hard to track down problems. When possible, it is "
"recommended to use the latter files, or ``pyproject.toml``, to hold your "
"pytest configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:156
msgid "Initialization: determining rootdir and configfile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:158
msgid ""
"pytest determines a ``rootdir`` for each test run which depends on the "
"command line arguments (specified test files, paths) and on the existence of "
"configuration files.  The determined ``rootdir`` and ``configfile`` are "
"printed as part of the pytest header during startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:163
msgid "Here's a summary what ``pytest`` uses ``rootdir`` for:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:165
msgid ""
"Construct *nodeids* during collection; each test is assigned a unique "
"*nodeid* which is rooted at the ``rootdir`` and takes into account the full "
"path, class name, function name and parametrization (if any)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:169
msgid ""
"Is used by plugins as a stable location to store project/test run specific "
"information; for example, the internal :ref:`cache <cache>` plugin creates a "
"``.pytest_cache`` subdirectory in ``rootdir`` to store its cross-test run "
"state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:173
msgid ""
"``rootdir`` is **NOT** used to modify ``sys.path``/``PYTHONPATH`` or "
"influence how modules are imported. See :ref:`pythonpath` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:176
msgid ""
"The :option:`--rootdir=path` command-line option can be used to force a "
"specific directory. Note that contrary to other command-line options, ``--"
"rootdir`` cannot be used with :confval:`addopts` inside a configuration file "
"because the ``rootdir`` is used to *find* the configuration file already."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:182
msgid "Finding the ``rootdir``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:184
msgid "Here is the algorithm which finds the rootdir from ``args``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:186
msgid ""
"If :option:`-c` is passed in the command-line, use that as configuration "
"file, and its directory as ``rootdir``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:188
msgid ""
"Determine the common ancestor directory for the specified ``args`` that are "
"recognised as paths that exist in the file system. If no such paths are "
"found, the common ancestor directory is set to the current working directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:192
msgid ""
"Look for ``pytest.toml``, ``.pytest.toml``, ``pytest.ini``, ``.pytest.ini``, "
"``pyproject.toml``, ``tox.ini``, and ``setup.cfg`` files in the ancestor "
"directory and upwards.  If one is matched, it becomes the ``configfile`` and "
"its directory becomes the ``rootdir``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:196
msgid ""
"If no configuration file was found, look for ``setup.py`` upwards from the "
"common ancestor directory to determine the ``rootdir``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:199
msgid ""
"If no ``setup.py`` was found, look for ``pytest.toml``, ``.pytest.toml``, "
"``pytest.ini``, ``.pytest.ini``, ``pyproject.toml``, ``tox.ini``, and "
"``setup.cfg`` in each of the specified ``args`` and upwards. If one is "
"matched, it becomes the ``configfile`` and its directory becomes the "
"``rootdir``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:203
msgid ""
"If no ``configfile`` was found and no configuration argument is passed, use "
"the already determined common ancestor as root directory. This allows the "
"use of pytest in structures that are not part of a package and don't have "
"any particular configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:207
msgid ""
"If no ``args`` are given, pytest collects test below the current working "
"directory and also starts determining the ``rootdir`` from there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:210
msgid "Files will only be matched for configuration if:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:212
msgid ""
"``pytest.toml``: will always match and take highest precedence, even if "
"empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:213
msgid ""
"``pytest.ini``: will always match and take precedence (after ``pytest.toml`` "
"and ``.pytest.toml``), even if empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:214
msgid ""
"``pyproject.toml``: contains a ``[tool.pytest]`` or ``[tool.pytest."
"ini_options]`` table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:215
msgid "``tox.ini``: contains a ``[pytest]`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:216
msgid "``setup.cfg``: contains a ``[tool:pytest]`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:218
msgid ""
"Finally, a ``pyproject.toml`` file will be considered the ``configfile`` if "
"no other match was found, in this case even if it does not contain a ``[tool."
"pytest]`` table (since version ``9.0``) or a ``[tool.pytest.ini_options]`` "
"table (since version ``8.1``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:222
msgid ""
"The files are considered in the order above. Options from multiple "
"``configfiles`` candidates are never merged - the first match wins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:225
msgid "The configuration file also determines the value of the ``rootpath``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:227
msgid ""
"The :class:`Config <pytest.Config>` object (accessible via hooks or through "
"the :fixture:`pytestconfig` fixture) will subsequently carry these "
"attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:230
msgid ""
":attr:`config.rootpath <pytest.Config.rootpath>`: the determined root "
"directory, guaranteed to exist. It is used as a reference directory for "
"constructing test addresses (\"nodeids\") and can be used also by plugins "
"for storing per-testrun information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:234
msgid ""
":attr:`config.inipath <pytest.Config.inipath>`: the determined "
"``configfile``, may be ``None`` (it is named ``inipath`` for historical "
"reasons)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:237
msgid ""
"The ``config.rootpath`` and ``config.inipath`` properties. They are :class:"
"`pathlib.Path` versions of the older ``config.rootdir`` and ``config."
"inifile``, which have type ``py.path.local``, and still exist for backward "
"compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:244
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:246
msgid "pytest path/to/testdir path/other/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:250
msgid ""
"will determine the common ancestor as ``path`` and then check for "
"configuration files as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:253
msgid ""
"# first look for path/pytest.toml\n"
"path/pytest.toml\n"
"path/pytest.ini\n"
"path/pyproject.toml  # must contain a [tool.pytest] table to match\n"
"path/tox.ini         # must contain [pytest] section to match\n"
"path/setup.cfg       # must contain [tool:pytest] section to match\n"
"pytest.toml\n"
"pytest.ini\n"
"... # all the way up to the root\n"
"\n"
"# now look for setup.py\n"
"path/setup.py\n"
"setup.py\n"
"... # all the way up to the root"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference/customize.rst:273
msgid ""
"Custom pytest plugin commandline arguments may include a path, as in "
"``pytest --log-output ../../test.log args``. Then ``args`` is mandatory, "
"otherwise pytest uses the folder of test.log for rootdir determination (see "
"also :issue:`1435`). A dot ``.`` for referencing to the current working "
"directory is also possible."
msgstr ""

